<p>State Farm's Guideline for External Associates Using Vendor and State Farm names in signature files</p>  
 
<p class="categoryHeading">Why this guideline is important to Systems:</p>
<ul> 
<li> This guideline aids in maintaining the appropriate use of vendor name in connection with State Farm business.</li> 
<li> This guideline is consistent with guideline R0183 - Use of State Farm Logos and Trademarks. </li>
</ul> 
<p class="categoryHeading">Guideline Specifics:</p> 
<ul>
<li>  External Associates are prohibited from using  vendor name and/or State Farm name in signature files that are used within State Farm email systems.</li>
</ul>
<p class="categoryHeading">Acceptable Usage examples:</p> 
        &nbsp;&nbsp;Bob External <br>
        &nbsp;&nbsp;(111) 111-1111 <br>
        &nbsp;&nbsp;Systems Project Development (SPD)<br><br> 
        &nbsp;&nbsp;Bob External <br>
		<table>
		<tr>
		<td width="200" valign="top">
        &nbsp;State Farm Forms team</td>
		<td width="300">(is used as a team name, not referring to State Farm 'the business')</td>
		</tr>
</table> <br>
<p class="categoryHeading">Unacceptable Usage examples:</p> 
        &nbsp;&nbsp;Bob External <br>
        &nbsp;&nbsp;(111) 111-1111 <br>
        &nbsp;&nbsp;ABCXYZ Company <br><br>
        &nbsp;&nbsp;Bob External <br>
        &nbsp;&nbsp;"ABCXYZ Company - providing 20 years of quality service"        <br><br>
        
        &nbsp;&nbsp;Bob External <br>
        &nbsp;&nbsp;State Farm Insurance Companies 
<p class="categoryHeading">Who is affected by the Guideline:</p> 
<ul>
<li>  External Associates 
</li>
</ul>

